    <h2>Introduction</h1>
      <p>India, officially known as the Republic of India, is a diverse and vibrant country located in South Asia. It is
        the seventh-largest country by land area and the second-most populous country in the world, with over 1.3
        billion people. India is renowned for its rich history, cultural heritage, and geographical diversity.The
        country shares its borders with several countries, including Pakistan, China, Nepal, Bhutan, Bangladesh, and
        Myanmar. The Indian subcontinent is surrounded by the Arabian Sea to the west, the Bay of Bengal to the east,
        and the Indian Ocean to the south.</p>
      <p>India has a parliamentary democratic system of government and is known as the largest democracy in the world.
        It consists of 28 states and 8 union territories, each with its own unique culture, language, and
        traditions.India is a popular tourist destination that attracts millions of visitors from around the globe each
        year. With its diverse landscapes, rich history, and vibrant culture, India offers a plethora of experiences for
        travelers.</p>
      <p>One of the most iconic landmarks in India is the Taj Mahal, located in the city of Agra. Built by Mughal
        Emperor Shah Jahan in memory of his beloved wife Mumtaz Mahal, the Taj Mahal is renowned for its stunning
        architecture and intricate marble craftsmanship.</p>
      <p>Other popular tourist destinations in India include the ancient city of Jaipur, known for its vibrant culture
        and magnificent palaces; the serene backwaters of Kerala, where visitors can cruise on traditional houseboats;
        and the spiritual city of Varanasi, situated on the banks of the sacred river Ganges.</p>
      <p>For nature lovers, India offers diverse landscapes ranging from the snow-capped peaks of the Himalayas to the
        sun-kissed beaches of Goa and the lush tea plantations of Darjeeling. Wildlife enthusiasts can explore India's
        national parks and wildlife sanctuaries, home to majestic creatures such as tigers, elephants, and rhinoceroses.
      </p>
      <p>India's culinary scene is as diverse as its culture, with each region offering its own unique flavors and
        specialties. From spicy street food to lavish feasts fit for royalty, Indian cuisine is sure to tantalize the
        taste buds of travelers.Whether you're seeking adventure, relaxation, or cultural immersion, India promises an
        unforgettable experience that will leave you mesmerized and craving for more.</p>
